                    </div>
                    <span>The Franco-Prussian War may be the most unknown of "modern" conflicts: like most people, I was aware that the French army was destroyed at Sedan, but knew little else. This book remedied that shortcoming. The author not only describes the campaigns in sufficient detail, he also is able to provide an overview that is most enligtening. It is fascinating to contemplate this war in light of the events of 1914 and 1940. This is simply an excellent book.</span>
                  
              
